DGM 1600
Professor Marty

1.	What is a variable?
  a.	A variable is used to store a certain type of value. The value can be changed later, but the type can’t. 
    i.	1 can be changed to 2, but not to an ‘a’.
2.	Describe declaration and initialization.
  a.	Declaration: declaring the name of the variable and its type.
  b.	Initialization: setting an initial value to the variable.
3.	Example of 2.
  a.	Declaration: 		int the_Value;
  b.	Initialization: 		the_Value = 0;
4.	Two types of variables.
  a.	int, double.
